---
import '../styles/global.css'
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy · Mathis Heck" description="Privacy information for Mathis Heck photography portfolio">
  <main class="container privacy">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>This website is operated by Mathis Heck. I keep analytics lightweight and privacy-friendly.</p>

    <section>
      <h2>Responsible</h2>
      <p>Mathis Heck · Trier · kontakt@mathisheck.de</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Analytics (Umami)</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Self-hosted on my VPS.</li>
        <li>No cookies, no local storage, no third-party sharing.</li>
        <li>Collected metrics: page views, referrer, device/browser type, approximate region/country, timestamps.</li>
        <li>IP addresses are anonymized; no personal profiles are created.</li>
        <li>Legal basis: legitimate interest (Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR) in running a privacy-friendly website.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Hosting</h2>
      <p>The site and analytics are hosted on my own server (VPS) in Frankfurt, Germany.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Data retention</h2>
      <p>Analytics data is retained for up to 12 months for aggregate statistics and then deleted.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <p>You can contact me at kontakt@mathisheck.de for access, deletion, or questions.</p>
    </section>
  </main>

  <style>
    .privacy {
      max-width: 780px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 5rem 1.5rem 4rem;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .privacy h1 {
      font-size: clamp(1.9rem, 3vw, 2.4rem);
      margin: 0 0 1rem;
    }

    .privacy h2 {
      margin: 1.8rem 0 0.6rem;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    }

    .privacy p,
    .privacy li {
      margin: 0.35rem 0;
      line-height: 1.65;
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .privacy ul {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
      margin: 0.2rem 0 0.6rem;
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
